ently debate whether the hosting market is saturated, oversaturated, polyunsaturated, or some other form of full. &nbsp;I think everyone agrees that it\u2019s not like the 1990s where if you could spell HTML you could sell hosting to a line of people seeking to Surf the Information Superhighway. &nbsp;But is there still opportunity for a hosting company to grow?</p><p>According to <a href=\"https://www.fortunebusinessinsights.com/enquiry/request-sample-pdf/web-hosting-services-market-100863\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\" aria-label=\"Fortune Business Report\">Fortune Business Insights</a>, who released a report recently entitle \u201cWeb Hosting Services Market, 2021-2028\u201d the answer is an unqualified yes.</p><p>The market is expected to grow to $267.1 billion, at a compounded annual growth rate of 18% over the next 7 years given its present $75 billion size.</p><p>The report lists the following growth drivers:</p><ul><li>Emergence of Hosting Services for Startups to Boost the Market</li><li>Incorporation of AI in Web Hosting Services to Open New Vistas for Market Growth</li><li>Agreements between Social Media Giants &amp; Web Service Companies to Intensify Competition.</li></ul><p>Well\u2026that\u2019s just how consultants talk. &nbsp;You can get a copy of the report <a href=\"https://www.globenewswire.com/Tracker?data=0i0Gzv-A5EEphTczaVtzOOa3y4ENlnC-DtsMT5HQu0DaOr_smLtdydd3Bzux8_WkOxN3w5HGguz5YVU6z_TEcKGO_deEuV73d81KZaAnTjtcG9gDztrmJGvWZF87k9BSHgOIbISu3XVyw1iziDVd0vC_N6paJ5a-HRLBl5Ok_1X0_4Yj9-s9p9MoJwyRSYV0ICsNoYS4mxSh7rF_I672gMVH0Z0N4BSrg-dm6dlKREhfSyRWk29oSR1_mfJRBdYSIVcZ6QnsZnwUhzpPSvJp9mUTXnnWaQfqpKh5Wn1sdnDy2KoHesrSJnzyOtYYynm5\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\" aria-label=\"Fortune Business Report\">here</a>.</p><div class=\"relpost-thumb-wrapper\"><div class=\"relpost-thumb-container\"><h3>Related posts:</h3><div style=\"clear: both\"></div><div style=\"clear: both\"></div><div class=\"relpost-block-container\"><a class=\"relpost-block-single\"